rComments: Only thing good about this guy is his chalkboard notes. Can't seem to explain anything clearly or in-depth, and made a simple fundamentals class a headache to understand which didn't help me throughout the rest of my degree. Tests were fair, just get some outside help or teach yourself.

He would go bananas on you if you try to take pictures of the board! He was very rude to me personally for some reason and he would not like it when I ask questions in the class. The worst grade I got during my studies at the University of Ottawa
Horrible is an understatement avoid if you can.

He really does a good job, he puts effort into his work which shows,  will give you feedback or reexplain concepts if you ask. Rating him any less than 8/10 is would be disrespectful IMO. Some questions he will make you think of the answer as to let you think for yourself which some people say make him feel a bit unapproachable. But 9.5/10 IMO.
Worst prof I've ever had in university.
